Detailed Description

Class WapProfileMgr holds the collection of all WAP Profiles.

There is 0 or 1 profile active. Though there is just one profile active, the id's and names of all WAP profiles are held in WapProfileInfo objects, for selection purposes.

  • WapProfileMgr is a manager class and does not carry out any interaction with the user.
  • WapProfileMgr does not hold browser specific settings such as fonts or colors.

BOOLEAN WapProfileMgr::CreateWapProfile (  WapProfile &  profile  ) 
 

Used to create a new Wap Profile. This method creates a unique profile id and sets it to the profile reference passed as argument. It returns FALSE if there are no free id to be assigned i.e., when the number of profiles has reached the maximum limit.

Parameters:
profile This profile reference is passed by the application to the WapProfileMgr class after instantiation for setting the identifier.
Returns:
TRUE - Success of Method FALSE - Failure of Method.
